      "id": "PopularPost109214",
      "post_content": "That's not true - the ruling is correct. If a creature with +1/+1 counters receives enough -1/-1 counters to reduce its toughness to 0 IN ONE GO (ie. Arcbound Worker is hit with a Distill Infection), then two state based actions are checked at the same time the next time a player gains priority: a creature with toughness 0 being sent to the graveyard, and +1/+1 and -1/-1 counters cancelling each other out. As the creature is sent to the graveyard at the same time the counters would be cancelled out the game still sees it as having had an appropriate number of +1/+1 counters, and as such they can be moved via modular.",
      "posted_by": "JaxsonBateman",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost109214\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">That's not true - the ruling is correct. If a creature with +1/+1 counters receives enough -1/-1 counters to reduce its toughness to 0 IN ONE GO (ie. Arcbound Worker is hit with a Distill Infection), then two state based actions are checked at the same time the next time a player gains priority: a creature with toughness 0 being sent to the graveyard, and +1/+1 and -1/-1 counters cancelling each other out. As the creature is sent to the graveyard at the same time the counters would be cancelled out the game still sees it as having had an appropriate number of +1/+1 counters, and as such they can be moved via modular.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '109214'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy6928\">JaxsonBateman</span>\r\n                                (10/11/2010 12:30:59 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postRating_starRating